  "dataFlow": "A build is triggered by one of four inputs: (1) human POST /api/build from the Next.js dashboard, (2) GitHub or Linear webhook to POST /api/webhook, (3) Linear Todo poller in autonomy.py firing every 5 minutes, or (4) a cron trigger from cron.py. In all cases, create_session() in sessions.py allocates a BuildSession object in the _sessions in-memory dict and persists a JSON checkpoint to disk. run_build() then executes sequentially: git clone the target repo into app/workspaces/{sid}/, PITER-classify the brief, inject relevant lessons from .harness/lessons.jsonl into the prompt context, invoke the Claude Agent SDK (_run_claude_via_sdk) with permission_mode=bypassPermissions, stream token events back to the caller via WebSocket (/ws/build/{sid}) or SSE (/api/sessions/{sid}/logs), then run the evaluator SDK session against the git diff. If the evaluator score passes the threshold (default 7/10), the session commits and pushes changes via git. All phase transitions write atomic JSON checkpoints. Terminal state (complete/failed/killed) is persisted and optionally logged to Supabase gate_checks table via supabase_log.py. Cron-triggered Pi-SEO scans write findings to .harness/scan-results/{project}/{date}.json; the monitor agent reads those files, computes health deltas, and persists digests to .harness/monitor-digests/; the triage engine converts critical/high findings into Linear tickets via the Linear GraphQL API. Inbound Telegram messages from Phill land in .harness/telegram-inbox/ via the polling script, are drained by the watchdog, classified, and either self-healed or escalated back to Telegram. The MCP server reads .harness/ files on demand and serves them to Claude Desktop over stdio JSON-RPC.",
